What does this props interface tell you about the Modal component?

```typescript
interface ModalProps {
  title: string;
  children: React.ReactNode;
  isOpen: boolean;
  onClose: () => void;
  size?: "sm" | "md" | "lg";
}
```

A developer wrote this component. What is wrong with how it is being used?

```typescript
interface ToastProps {
  message: string;
  type: "success" | "error" | "warning";
  duration?: number;
  onDismiss: () => void;
}

function Toast({ message, type, duration = 3000, onDismiss }: ToastProps) {
  // ... component logic
}

// Usage:
<Toast
  message="Profile updated"
  type="info"
  onDismiss={() => setShowToast(false)}
/>
```

You are reviewing a PR and see this component interface. The designer asks: what configuration options does this table support?

```typescript
interface Column<T> {
  key: keyof T;
  header: string;
  render?: (value: T[keyof T], row: T) => React.ReactNode;
  sortable?: boolean;
  width?: string;
}

interface DataTableProps<T> {
  data: T[];
  columns: Column<T>[];
  onRowClick?: (row: T) => void;
  isLoading?: boolean;
  emptyMessage?: string;
  sortBy?: string;
  sortDirection?: "asc" | "desc";
}
```

What would you tell the designer?
